post_text:
Currently exploring the option of installing a completely wireless LTE network throughout the entirety of our USD290 district boundaries. Those homes that are within our boundary would be provided with free Internet access, via the use of a small cellular modem. This modem device would plug directly into the computer and allow access to the Internet anywhere within range of our towers.

We need as many residents in our district boundaries to fill this form out to help us make this a reality! We have funding available. There would be zero additional financial impact to taxpayers beyond the potential cost of the modem device. This is made possible by advances in technology, and the Kansas State Department of Commerce Connectivity Emergency Response Grant (CERG).

post_text:
USD 290 Parents,

Yesterday afternoon, Governor Kelly mandated that masks be worn in all public spaces. As our summer programs continue and others get ready to start, please be aware that in order to comply with the Governor's order, we will be asking all students and staff to wear masks while attending summer school and driver's education, both of which begin on July 6th. We will have masks available, however, they are in short supply. We would ask that if you have a mask for your student that you send them with it each day. If you have concerns about attending these programs, please contact your building principals to discuss the different options that might exist.

On Wednesday, I will meet with the Franklin County Health Officer to review our weight and summer conditioning programs and how the Governor's order impacts what we do there. Once we have further clarification on what we need to do, we will address that with both our parents and students.

Again, thank you for your patience and understanding as well as your support.

Ryan Cobbs

post_text:
USD 290 parents, as we begin to prepare for the 2020/21 school year we recognize that there is still a great deal of uncertainty regarding how school might operate. The Kansas State Department of Education is set to release their guidelines for reopening to schools on July 9th. As we discuss our options and how we can best operate under those guidelines, I wanted to make sure that we get some input from our parents as to your comfort level and concerns regarding the opening of school in August. Below is a link to a google form that I would invite you to fill out so that we can best be prepared to meet the needs of our students and families once we know for sure what the expectations of the State are. I appreciate your time, your input, your patience with us, and as always, your support.

Link to survey: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSczT2gbAuSKWD4YOfrgDb6iIaF-UOmqOeZ3AvNMNiaC7EAwGg/viewform?vc=0&c=0&w=1

Sincerely,

Dr. Ryan Cobbs

Good morning parents and staff. As we continue to progress through these unusual times there are still items that we must turn our attention to to ensure that we are not impacted negatively by them in the future. Currently, the 2020 Census is one of those issues. Even though there are matters in our lives taking precedence over nearly everything else, it is still important for us to do our part for our community and our state through the census. I have attached some information here that may be helpful as you complete your part.
Thank you and have a great day!

**Households can still respond online - To do that, they go to the census website (www.my2020census.gov) and right underneath the place to enter a code is a link that says "If you do not have a Census ID, click here." A person can click on that and enter their physical address then continue on with the survey.
Households can also call 844-330-2020 to provide their responses.

post_text: Good morning everyone. At a time when good news seems to be at a premium I wanted to let everyone know that USD 290 has finalized a bond refinance that will save taxpayers $9.6 million dollars over the life of our construction bonds! It also allows us to complete bond payments 4 years in advance zeroing our bond balance in 2036 instead of 2040! Thank you USD 290 patrons for providing such incredible spaces for our kids and our community!

At a time when good news seems to be at a premium I wanted to let everyone know that USD 290 has finalized a bond refinance that will save taxpayers $9.6 million dollars over the life of our construction bonds! Thank you USD 290 patrons for providing such incredible spaces for our kids and our community!

post_text: Mrs. Stinebaugh, Aldan Michael, Quinncy Morris, and Ryley Meyerkorth participated in KU's Night at the Lab. These students came in early every morning for several weeks in preparation for this event which is intended to help students draw connections between health and science and showcase that knowledge to the community. Our students participated at the regional event in Lawrence on October 24 and have qualified to represent Ottawa High School at the State event at KU Medical Center on November 18 and 19.

The sale will end at Midnight on November 19th.

Order by November 19th to receive shipment by the week of December 17th- 21st.

post_text: Reach for the Stars After School has open positions for group leaders. RFTS operates Monday through Thursday from 3:15 to 5:45. We offer flexible work schedules around school schedules. Approximately 10 hours available each week. Starting pay of $13/hour for those who have graduated high school.. This is a perfect job for students with Education or Human Services majors. Experience working with children is a plus but not mandatory. If you are interested, please go to USD290 under employment opportunities and look for 21st Century. For questions, please contact Jamie Keiter at keiterj@usd290.org.

All kindergarten families need to come to enrollment on August 1st at your elementary building to enroll your kindergarten student. Students attend the elementary based on their address. To check for your boundary school: http://ohsweb.usd290.org/maps/boundaries.html
